Text: Re whats upPST Phil I have been really busy the last couple of weeks Well come to think of it I have been really busy ever since I started this job Yesterday I was in Town and Country at am then straight to Edna Texas by am then straight to the Woodlands by pm and got back to the house last night about pm That has been a pretty typical day when in Houston and this morning I was up at am to catch the first flight into Austin Thankfully the hard work and long hours are paying off I have closed or deals now on my own and am further along then they expected me to be at this point so I will be in Houston on a more fulltime basis in the next couple of weeks I will be in Houston on my own all next week July th week By the end of July I should only be in Austin on Mondays as a day trip and then in Houston the rest of the week I have not yet purchased my airline tickets for the fishing trip but I will look to do it this weekend Good to hear you are doing well at work If you need to get in touch with me here are all my numbers Houston office Austin office or mobile email address or Talk to you soon Brian Havent talked to you in a while I dont have any of your numbers and I never know when you are in town How are things going Still loving that JOB Have you got your tickets for fly fishing yet Better hurry I can not wait for a little relaxation Bid week is over today and I will have some more time luckily Give me a shout PL
